<h2>Need an upgrade?</h2>
<h3>Buying new parts for your PC is a great way to boost performance without breaking the bank!</h3>
</br>
<h4 style="font-size:30; font-weight:bold">Is your computer just too slow?</h4>
	<ul>
		<li><span style="font-size:21px; font-weight:bold">Grab more RAM!</span></br>
		RAM (random access memory) gives your computer the ability to work on more tasks at once. If your computer easily gets overworked, getting more RAM will allow you to work on more at once without your computer slowing or crashing all together. PC Repair Utah <a href="https://www.digitaltrends.com/computing/how-much-ram-does-your-pc-need-probably-less-than-you-think/" traget="_blank">recommends</a> 8 gigabytes of RAM for the average user, and 16 gigabytes for heavier use.</li>
		<li><span style="font-size:21px; font-weight:bold">Time for a Solid State Drive!</span></br>
		Your computer likely has an old hard disk drive in it. Due to their mechanical nature, they are the slowest piece of your computer system. SSDs (solid state drives) are the future of storage. Getting an SSD will <i>hugely</i> <a href="http://www.pcworld.com/article/2048120/benchmarks-dont-lie-ssd-upgrades-deliver-huge-performance-gains.html" target="_blank">improve</a> the general speed of your computer, from boot times to loading and saving files. It'll feel like a brand new computer!</li>
	</ul>
